---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import SqlFormatter from '../../components/tools/SqlFormatter';
---

<ToolLayout
  title="SQL Formatter — Free Online SQL Beautifier"
  description="Format and beautify SQL queries with support for PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite, T-SQL, and PL/SQL dialects. All processing happens in your browser."
  toolName="SQL Formatter"
  toolUrl="https://oortcraft.dev/tools/sql-formatter"
  faq={[
    {
      question: 'Which SQL dialects are supported?',
      answer: 'SQL Formatter supports Standard SQL, PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite, T-SQL (Microsoft SQL Server), and PL/SQL (Oracle). Select your dialect from the toolbar before formatting to get dialect-specific keyword and syntax handling.',
    },
    {
      question: 'What formatting options are available?',
      answer: 'You can Format your SQL into readable, indented code with uppercase keywords and consistent spacing, or Minify it into a single compact line by collapsing all whitespace — useful for embedding SQL in configs or reducing payload size.',
    },
    {
      question: 'Is my SQL data safe?',
      answer: 'Yes. All formatting and minification happens entirely in your browser using JavaScript. No SQL is ever sent to a server, logged, or stored. Your queries remain completely private.',
    },
  ]}
>
  <div slot="tool">
    <SqlFormatter client:load />
  </div>
  <Fragment slot="content">
    <h2>How to Use the SQL Formatter</h2>
    <p>Paste your SQL query in the left panel, select your target dialect, then click <strong>Format</strong> to beautify or <strong>Minify</strong> to compact. Use the copy button to grab the result. All processing happens in your browser with no server round-trips.</p>

    <h2>Supported SQL Dialects</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Standard SQL</strong> — ANSI-compliant SQL for general use</li>
      <li><strong>PostgreSQL</strong> — Optimized for PostgreSQL-specific syntax and functions</li>
      <li><strong>MySQL</strong> — Handles MySQL and MariaDB dialect quirks</li>
      <li><strong>SQLite</strong> — Lightweight dialect used in embedded applications</li>
      <li><strong>T-SQL</strong> — Microsoft SQL Server and Azure SQL Database syntax</li>
      <li><strong>PL/SQL</strong> — Oracle Database procedural SQL extensions</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <h3>Which SQL dialects are supported?</h3>
    <p>SQL Formatter supports Standard SQL, PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite, T-SQL (Microsoft SQL Server), and PL/SQL (Oracle). Select your dialect from the toolbar before formatting to get dialect-specific keyword handling.</p>
    <h3>What formatting options are available?</h3>
    <p>Format produces readable, indented SQL with uppercase keywords. Minify collapses all whitespace into a single compact line — useful for configs or reducing payload size.</p>
    <h3>Is my SQL data safe?</h3>
    <p>Yes. All formatting happens entirely in your browser. No SQL is ever sent to a server, logged, or stored.</p>
  </Fragment>
</ToolLayout>
